Zero-Shot Prompting:
Def:
Zero-shot prompting means giving a task to an AI without any examples. The model answers using only its pre-trained knowledge.
When to Use:
When the task is simple or common
When you donâ€™t have example data
For quick responses or general questions
Input:
Translate the following sentence into French:
"I love learning AI."
Output:
J'aime apprendre l'IA.
___________
Few-shot Prompting:
Def:
Few-shot prompting means giving the AI a few examples before asking it to solve a similar task.
When to Use:
When the task is complex or specific
When you want better accuracy
When format or style is important
Input:
Translate English to French:

English: Hello
French: Bonjour

English: Thank you
French: Merci

English: I love learning AI
French:

Output:
J'aime apprendre l'IA.
________
Role-Based Prompting:
Def:
Assigning the specific role or persona to the AI (such as teacher, doctor, programmer, interviewer, storyteller, etc.) so it responds from that perspective, using relevant tone, knowledge, and behavior.
why it works:
ðŸŽ¯ Guides behavior â€“ the AI knows how to think and respond
ðŸ§  Improves accuracy by narrowing the context
ðŸ—£ï¸ Controls tone & style (formal, friendly, technical, simple)
âš¡ Reduces ambiguity and irrelevant answers
ðŸ“š Matches real-world expertise expectations
input:
Act as a machine learning teacher.
Explain overfitting in simple terms with an example.
output:
Overfitting happens when a machine learning model learns the training data too well, including noise, and performs poorly on new data.
For example, if a student memorizes answers instead of understanding concepts, they may fail a new exam. Similarly, an overfitted model fails on unseen data.
