Tools and Resources:

Development Tools

  Playgrounds & APIs:Interactive platforms and programming interfaces used to test, experiment, and deploy prompts with large language models.
  Testing Frameworks:Tools that help systematically test, compare, and validate prompt outputs for correctness, consistency, and regressions.
  Orchestration:Frameworks that coordinate multiple prompts, tools, and model calls into structured workflows or pipelines.
  Evaluation Libraries:Libraries used to measure and score model outputs based on accuracy, relevance, consistency, or other metrics.

Learning Resources

  Official Guides:Authoritative documentation provided by AI organizations explaining best practices, APIs, and prompting techniques.
  Seminal Papers:Foundational research papers that introduce or formalize key prompting and reasoning methods in AI.
  Advanced Methods:Specialized prompting strategies that improve reasoning, accuracy, or task performance beyond basic prompting.
  Community & Courses:Online groups, forums, and structured courses where learners share knowledge, learn prompting skills, and discuss advancements.
